OL,3,CJersey mother calls for clarity over
OL,4,Cisland's dyslexia support
OL,6,FAlthough neither the Government nor
OL,7,Fthe AEP has confirmed what the cause
OL,8,Fof the dispute is, the Government has
OL,9,Fcommissioned an independent external
OL,10,Fassessment of the services currently
OL,11,Fprovided.
OL,13,FJersey's government says there are
OL,14,Finterventions available for children
OL,15,Fwith literacy difficulties, which
OL,16,Fusually a Special Educational Needs
OL,17,FCoordinator offering their support.
OL,19,FIn a statement, Jersey's Commissioner
OL,20,Ffor Children and Young People, Dr
OL,21,FCarmel Corrigan, says:
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
