OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F388A1730967176
OL,3,CJersey mother calls for clarity over
OL,4,Cisland's dyslexia support
OL,6,F"We know from our own work with
OL,7,Fchildren and young people just how
OL,8,Fimportant it is to have accessible,
OL,9,Ffunctional support services in place
OL,10,Ffor children who have additional
OL,11,Fneeds. Not providing such assessment
OL,12,Fand support creates discrimination and
OL,13,Finequality in the education system and
OL,14,Fmarginalises these children.
OL,16,F"My hope is that this dispute can be
OL,17,Fresolved through constructive dialogue
OL,18,Fbetween the Association and the
OL,19,FGovernment of Jersey ` but there can
OL,20,Fbe no delay in this process: that
OL,21,Fconversation must start now."
